Samples

Overview
--------
This directory separates three different things that used to get mixed
together:

  production shards
      ->
  logical analysis samples
      ->
  per-run dataset assembly

The XML stages from the legacy production workflow are production shards.
They should stay here, not leak into downstream analysis sample keys.

Files
-----
datasets.tsv
  One row per dataset context.
  Fields:
    dataset_key  context  base_dir  list_dir

catalog.tsv
  One row per concrete shard-level member of a logical sample manifest.
  Fields:
    dataset_key  artifact_key  logical_key  source_kind  source_ref
    origin  variation  nominal  tag  role  defname  campaign  beam  polarity

  Meanings:
    dataset_key
      Dataset alias used by `samples-dag.mk` and the generated manifests.

    artifact_key
      One concrete shard-level list/build input.
      Examples: `beam-s0`, `ext-p1`, `beam-s0-sce`.

    logical_key
      The logical downstream sample key to build in `DatasetIO`.
      Repeated logical keys are merged by `mk_dataset --manifest`.

    source_kind
      Where the shard file list comes from.
      Supported values:
        `dir`
          Scan `base_dir/source_ref` with `tools/mklist.sh --dir`.
        `list`
          Reuse and normalise an existing list file with
          `tools/mklist.sh --list`.
        `samdef`
          Resolve a SAM definition to concrete PNFS file paths with
          `tools/mklist.sh --samdef`.

    source_ref
      Source-specific reference used by `source_kind`.
      Examples:
        `beam/s0/out`
        `samplelists/run1/beam-s0.list`
        `nl_run1_fhc_detvar_sce_goodruns`

    origin / variation / beam / polarity
      Shard-level `mk_sample` metadata.

    nominal / tag / role / defname / campaign
      Logical-sample metadata later stamped through `mk_dataset --defs`.

Generated outputs
-----------------
Run:

  bash tools/render-sample-catalog.sh

That writes plain-text generated files under `samples/generated/`:

  datasets.mk
    Richer include for `samples-dag.mk` with per-artifact list-generation
    overrides plus one logical `mk_sample` manifest per downstream sample key.

  <dataset>.<logical>.sample.manifest
    Plain-text shard membership for the native
    `mk_sample --sample <logical> --manifest ...` path.

  <dataset>.sample.defs
    Logical-sample metadata for `mk_dataset --defs`.

  <dataset>.dataset.manifest
    Logical-key to logical-sample-root manifest for `mk_dataset --manifest`.

Example workflow
----------------
Generate the derived files:

  bash tools/render-sample-catalog.sh

Build logical `SampleIO` files from the generated manifests:

  make -f samples-dag.mk DATASETS_FILE=samples/generated/datasets.mk samples

Assemble all logical datasets described by the generated manifests:

  make -f samples-dag.mk DATASETS_FILE=samples/generated/datasets.mk datasets

Or assemble one logical dataset directly:

  build/bin/mk_dataset \
    --defs samples/generated/run1_fhc.sample.defs \
    --campaign run1_fhc_v08_00_00_82 \
    --run run1 \
    --beam numi \
    --polarity fhc \
    --manifest samples/generated/run1_fhc.dataset.manifest \
    build/datasets/run1_fhc.root

Notes
-----
The native `mk_dataset` path consumes already-logical sample roots with an
explicit run / beam / polarity scope. The older positional
`sample-key=sample.root` workflow still works as a compatibility bridge.

`samples-dag.mk`
  Still accepts the old `artifact:subdir` include shape from `datasets.mk`.
  The richer generated path now emits explicit `logical_samples.*`,
  `sample_manifest.*`, `sample_artifacts.*`, `sample_source_kind.*`, and
  `sample_source_ref.*` variables instead.

`tools/mklist.sh --samdef`
  Requires `samweb` on `PATH`. This is the intended honest path for detector
  variations when the local source material only pins down a SAM definition and
  not a produced ntuple output directory.

The intended downstream keys are logical keys like:

  beam
  dirt
  ext
  signal
  beam-sce

not shard keys like:

  beam-s0
  beam-s1
  ext-p0
